    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — tracing Jeremiah's argument in its historical and canonical setting. Jeremiah 8 belongs to the scroll of early oracles (chs. 2-10) addressed to Judah before and during the early phase of Babylonian encroachment (roughly 627-605 BC). The movements below follow the chapter's own argument structure: from judgment oracle through ironic indictment to prophetic lament. Where Hebrew vocabulary sharpens the English, a brief note follows.",
